  </div>


  <h3>Orientation</h3>
  <p>Orientation is about users understanding where they are and where else they could go. Your IA lets them know if they're in the right place and what else might be of interest to them.</p>
  <div class="app-example app-example--content">
    <strong class="nhsuk-tag app-example__heading">Example</strong>
   <p>On the NHS website, the global navigation (like the main navigation bar) helps users orient themselves. So do local navigation structures like:</p>
   <ul>
    <li>hub pages</li>
    <li>breadcrumbs</li>
    <li>page titles</li>
    <li>headings</li>
  </ul>

   <figure class="nhsuk-image nhsuk-u-margin-top-6">
      <img class="nhsuk-image__img" src="/assets/orientation-v2.png" alt="Image of two different hub pages">
      <figcaption class="nhsuk-image__caption">
        Image showing two levels of hub pages with breadcrumbs and headings TBC
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>

  <h3>Navigation</h3>
  <p>Your IA helps users get to where they need to go. It gives them a good information scent to follow to find the content they need.</p>
  <div class="nhsuk-inset-text nhsuk-u-margin-top-4">
    <h4 id="information-scent">Information scent</h4>
    <p>Users pick up visual and textual cues about the content a website contains, including from its IA and link labels. These help them estimate the value of following a link.</p>
    <p>Users follow an information scent from what they see, but they also rely on what they already know.</p>
  </div>
   <div class="app-example app-example--content">
    <strong class="nhsuk-tag app-example__heading">Example</strong>
   <p>On the NHS website, global navigation structures, like the main navigation bar, help users browse to their destination. So do local navigation structures, like hub pages or page to page navigation.</p>


   <figure class="nhsuk-image nhsuk-u-margin-top-6">
      <img class="nhsuk-image__img" src="/assets/navigation.png" alt="Links at the bottom of a page to get to related content">
      <figcaption class="nhsuk-image__caption">
       Image showing nav structures that support navigation TBC
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>

  <h3>Search</h3>
  <p>Search helps users locate things that are more difficult to find.</p>
  <p>Organising your content and making it easy to navigate is vital for on-site search and helps Google understand it.</p>
     <div class="app-example app-example--content">
    <strong class="nhsuk-tag app-example__heading">Example</strong>
   <p>The work done to document hierarchies and the relationships between content on the NHS website underpin the site search engine and content management system (CMS).</p>
   <figure class="nhsuk-image nhsuk-u-margin-top-6">
      <img class="nhsuk-image__img" src="/assets/search.png" alt="image showing a search bar">
      <figcaption class="nhsuk-image__caption">
        Image of a search bar
