  </div>

  <h3>Placemaking, orientation, navigation and search rely on consistent navigation systems</h3>
  <p>Consistency builds trust. It's also to vital for accessibility.</p>
  <p>Hub pages, breadcrumbs and menus must work together to provide a consistent navigation system across every page of your website. That way all users have access to the structures that let them find what they need, wherever they are on the site.</p>
  <p>Different users use different navigation methods at different times. Your IA needs to give users multiple ways to do the same thing. For example, to go "up" a level, they might use:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>a breadcrumb</li>
    <li>page-to-page navigation</li>
    <li>the back button</li>
  </ul>
    <div class="app-example app-example--content">
    <strong class="nhsuk-tag app-example__heading">Example</strong>
   <p>The NHS website's content management system (CMS) uses templates for navigational hubs and content pages with page-to-page navigation. Teams use these templates and the same components and patterns consistently across the site.</p>
